16/ü§ìAlways DYOR (Do Your Own Research!)

Is the price of a NFT justified by the community, the quality of the team, the roadmap, the utility offered, the number of items in the collection, and so on?

Always ask yourself these questions before apeing in!

15/ When minting NFTs, be wary of collections that start with a high price or ones that are pushed by hype

If the original mint price is very high without much justification, then it's likely the NFT project may be a cash grab

14/ Also, be careful when buying NFTs in bundles on OpenSea as many people have ended up with fakes

Always check each item in a bundle before buying!

13/ If a deal is too good to be true, then it's probably a scam!

If someone said they've found valuable NFTs for way below the floor price, it's too good to be true and highly likely to be a scam

12/ Another example of a copycat collectionüëá

The scammers used a screenshot of the Bored Ape Yacht Club logo with the certified checkmark

Notice for this fake Bored Ape Yacht Club collection, the verified checkmark is not next the name of the project on the individual items https://t.co/G5Utcfs1Dz

11/ Many NFT projects have copycats that look similar to the genuine collections

For example, scammers use similar names or screenshots of legit project's logos with the verified checkmark to dupe buyers

üîñBookmark the pages of your favourite collections to avoid this scam

10/ üîçMake sure you know the accurate contract address of the NFT you are buying, which can be checked on @etherscan and is used to verify the authenticity

Go to details section on OpenSea to compare the contract address with the one on the project's website or Discord https://t.co/e7sTTtLCYk

9/ Following our presale, we‚Äôve seen many copycat Rollbot collections on OpenSea

This is the genuine link to the Rollbot collection on OpenSea: https://t.co/L4KVYXSK8P 

Always use the official links from our Discord. Anything else is a scam!

8/ Another form of impersonation: fake NFT collections

Always check you are buying NFTs from verified collections 

On OpenSea, individual items will have the checkmark next to their name for verified collections

7/ Impersonation is another trick that scammers pullü•∏

They'll try to convince you they're someone else, e.g., a founder of a NFT project to win your trust

If they asking you for any sort of favour (to open a link, or asking for crypto or your seed phrase), that's a red flagüö©

6/ If you have a significant amount invested in NFTs, you should own and use a hardware wallet

Hardware wallets (like Ledger) will protect your private key from any exploits related to MetaMask

It'll minimise your attack surface and the likelihood of getting hacked

5/ Why should you never store your seed phrase on your computerüñ•Ô∏è?

Because if you accidentally download malicious software, hackers will be able to access your computer and all of the files on it

Only download trusted software and avoid opening any suspicious files

4/ Do not store the seed phrase on your computer, in the cloud or in a password manager

‚úíÔ∏èWrite it down and keep it in a safe place where no one can find it

You may also want to split up your seed phrase across several pieces of paper for additional security

3/ Storing your NFT securely is also importantüîí

Active 2FA on your Rollbit account!

The most popular wallet for NFTs is MetaMaskü¶ä: https://t.co/heRXa5EzgL

All someone needs to access your account is your seed phrase/private key, so NEVER type these anywhere or share them

2/ Be wary of phishing sitesüé£

Double check every link that you click on, avoid clicking links from DMs or Twitter

Scammers will send links that look like NFT-related domains like OpenSea, minting pages and so on

üîñBookmark all genuine NFT websites

18/ We're excited to become the first casino to launch an NFT with unrivalled utility and will hold our presale in just 7 days time: https://t.co/Pgc88Z3sVv

The events in 2021 so far are just the beginning for NFTs and we're excited to become part of this fast-growing industry!

17/ We believe utility NFTs will be the next sector to pop

Because of their nature, they will attract much more interest as their potential is realised in the coming months and offer much more longevity due to the use cases they unlock

16/ Another avenue for brands to connect with their customers is through utility NFTs, which provide some sort of real-world value for holding the token

Think loyalty programs, revenue sharing, and much more but on the blockchain instead of a centralised database

15/ Crypto-native businesses are also using metaverses to advertise their services and launch virtual HQs to connect with their customers in a novel way

This is just one aspect of how NFTs allows brands to connect with their customers that have never existed before

14/ Metaverses (or virtual worlds) are also opening up new opportunities, providing exciting new ways to advertise and socialise

e.g, @SnoopDogg recently announced his own private party in one of the most popular Metaverses, @decentraland

13/ Traditional games like Fortnite are walled gardens

You can buy in-game assets, but you do not truly own them unless you can also trade them with other players

NFT gaming projects are making that possible, opening up a whole new world of possibilities for gamers

12/ While art NFTs are a big leap for creators, a similar advancement is being made in the gaming universe 

NFTs are giving players the opportunity to earn income for their hobby and have their say in how games evolve, as well as true ownership of in-game assets

11/ Other than investors, NFTs also represent an incredible opportunity for artists and musicians

A revolutionary aspect of NFTs are 'programmed royalties'

Smart contracts allow artists to get their fair dues each time their work is sold with royalties paid out automatically

10/ NFTs are also modernising art, a centuries old store value

But physical pieces can be fake, the ownership history may be opaque and trades involve complicated logistics

The art market is estimated to be worth ~$65 billion, with NFTs potentially capturing this value

9/ The global collectibles market is estimated to be worth around $370 billion!

NFTs are set to expand this market as well as modernise it, bringing it up to speed with the digital age

8/ The OG NFTs have begun to acquire the status of long-term stores of value, with big investors buying up the rarest pieces in the past few months, boosting valuations

e.g., A CryptoPunk that was initially free to claim is now worth hundreds of thousands of dollars!

7/ The first popular NFTs were collectibles, beginning with Rare Pepes and CryptoPunks during the crypto bull market of 2016-2018

Since then these NFTs have become the ultimate flexüí™allowing wealthy individuals to display their status to millions of people online

6/ Any smart contract blockchain can support NFTs

#Ethereum dominates in terms of market share

Other competitor chains include #Avalanche, #Cardano, #Flow, #Solana and #WAX

5/ Some examples:

ü™ôCollectibles: CryptoPunks, @BoredApeYC & @nbatopshot 
üé®Art: @artblocks_io & @SuperRare 
üé∂Music: @AudiusProject 
üéÆGaming: @AxieInfinity, @illuviumio & @staratlas 
üåêMetaverses: @TheSandboxGame & @decentraland 
üîßUtility: @ensdomains & @unstoppableweb

4/ All that is required is an internet connection and some crypto to achieve true ownership of art, collectibles, decentralised domain names, in-game items, music, virtual real estate (and much more), all of which can be represented by NFTs

3/ Their scarcity can be cryptographically proven, and since NFTs are digital, they can live forever on the blockchain

Compared to their physical counterparts, it's also much easier to transfer NFTs, which can be done at any time, anywhere, without a middleman

2/ Each Non-Fungible Token (NFT) is built on a smart contract that contains specific information making it unique, with the code verifying that it is the only digital asset with certain characteristics
